							<h3 class="invis">Author bio</h3>
																																															<a href="https://hakaimagazine.com/profiles/jess-craig/" class="tagmanager" id="author_link_bottom" >
											<div class="container col3 ">
												<div class="col span2"><p>Jess Craig is an independent multimedia journalist and foreign correspondent primarily covering science, global health, development, and environmental topics. Craig has a special interest in Indigenous communities and post-conflict settings. Craig holds undergraduate degrees in microbiology and writing and a Master’s degree in biostatistics.</p></div>
												<div class="singlebioimage col nomobile"><img width="400" height="400" src="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/jess-craig.jpg" class="attachment-medium size-medium wp-post-image" alt="writer Jess Craig" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/jess-craig.jpg 400w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/jess-craig-150x150.jpg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /></div>
